raw_data.title: HVAC Technician
raw_data.description: The HVAC Technician will troubleshoot, install, repair, and maintain assigned HVAC equipment, and properly communicate with customers to assure the company’s high-quality reputation is maintained. Responsibilities include: preventive maintenance, troubleshooting, rooftop units, chillers, cooling towers, hot water/steam boiler, packaged air conditioners, computer room AC equipment, control systems, air handling/fan coil units, condensers/chilled water pumps, refrigerated air dryers, air compressors, exhaust fans, ice machines, variable frequency drives, humidifiers.
raw_data.education_and_experience_substitution: GED may be substituted for High School Diploma

labor_categories.years_experience: GED may be substituted for High School Diploma
